The paper deals with algorithmic properties of switching classes, which are related to graph structures and their properties. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves combinatorial and algebraic properties of switching classes, which suggests categories such as cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also discusses the diameter and maximum matching of graphs, which are numerical problems, indicating the category cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper involves graph theory, which suggests the category cs.GT (Graph Theory).
